00:50:14.050 --> 00:50:17.650
So like I said, the polygamist
law was passed in 1892,

00:50:17.650 --> 00:50:22.770
and it was against Mormons who
were coming in through Mexico.

00:50:22.770 --> 00:50:26.260
So and it was to bar them
from entering the US.

00:50:26.260 --> 00:50:29.700
So I mean, if you take this sort
of writ large, there were concerns,

00:50:29.700 --> 00:50:34.490
there were strong concerns against
Catholics, even, from Italy,

00:50:34.490 --> 00:50:38.930
and from Ireland, even though at
that point the Irish had lived

00:50:38.930 --> 00:50:41.410
in the US for a longer time.

00:50:41.410 --> 00:50:45.940
And from Eastern Europe, you have
Slavs, some of whom are Muslim,

00:50:45.940 --> 00:50:48.540
some of whom are Eastern Orthodox.

00:50:48.540 --> 00:50:51.740
All, even the Eastern Orthodox,
and that's what sort of interesting

00:50:51.740 --> 00:50:55.400
to me when I'm reading this,
were really considered outsiders.

00:50:55.400 --> 00:51:02.800
That there was a fear of Eastern
Orthodox, not to the extent maybe

00:51:02.800 --> 00:51:09.070
of Muslims, but there were fears
that a WASP nation was changing.

00:51:09.070 --> 00:51:13.210
So the quotas that I was just
mentioning that were enacted,

00:51:13.210 --> 00:51:19.740
were based on the 1890 census,
which is a long time before 1924.

00:51:19.740 --> 00:51:21.970
And the reason that they
were picking that is

00:51:21.970 --> 00:51:27.810 position:56%
because the Congress wanted the type
of immigrants that came in in 1890,

00:51:27.810 --> 00:51:31.560
who were traditionally
Western Northern Europeans.

00:51:31.560 --> 00:51:36.360
So that plays into your question
about religion, because, in fact,

00:51:36.360 --> 00:51:40.980
religion was a factor in excluding
people, and particularly Asians.

00:51:40.980 --> 00:51:43.870
I mean, I think that although
I'm looking at MENA's,

00:51:43.870 --> 00:51:46.890
Asians really had it really rough.

00:51:46.890 --> 00:51:49.190
In the back?

