00:52:40.320 --> 00:52:45.520
And they did borrow a little
bit from the Armenian success.

00:52:45.520 --> 00:52:48.020
So there were 2 cases,
one was earlier

00:52:48.020 --> 00:52:49.890
and then one was in the 1920s.

00:52:49.890 --> 00:52:52.980
And the Armenians were
very successful, right,

00:52:52.980 --> 00:52:55.700
in not having it come back.

00:52:55.700 --> 00:52:59.780
So they petitioned, and they
were granted naturalization,

00:52:59.780 --> 00:53:02.550
and they became US citizens
through these cases.

00:53:02.550 --> 00:53:05.410
And it is similar to the MENA
cases that I'm looking at,

00:53:05.410 --> 00:53:07.300 position:56%
particularly Syrian Christian cases.

00:53:07.300 --> 00:53:10.350
Because once again, their
Christianity is not sort

00:53:10.350 --> 00:53:12.390
of accepted as being the norm.

00:53:12.390 --> 00:53:15.760
And the norm meaning a Protestant,

00:53:15.760 --> 00:53:19.510
a vague Protestant norm,
a WASP type of norm.

00:53:19.510 --> 00:53:24.120
And so as Eastern Christians,

00:53:24.120 --> 00:53:27.090
they also faced discrimination
on the same basis.

00:53:27.090 --> 00:53:30.550
I believe they used the
same anthropologists.

00:53:30.550 --> 00:53:35.730
So the anthropologists would go in
and look at where the peoples were

00:53:35.730 --> 00:53:38.290
and how that related to
the Caucus Mountains.

00:53:38.290 --> 00:53:42.850
So that actually kind of served
the Armenians quite well, right.

00:53:42.850 --> 00:53:46.340
But there was also this
proximity to the Caucus Mountains

00:53:46.340 --> 00:53:50.560
that was also used,
especially in the earlier cases,

00:53:50.560 --> 00:53:54.620
where biological origins
were emphasized more.

00:53:54.620 --> 00:53:56.420
Yes?

00:53:56.420 --> 00:54:07.330
