00:54:07.330 --> 00:54:11.690
The question is, how do I classify
polygamy as cultural or religious.

00:54:11.690 --> 00:54:16.960
I mean, I actually believe it's
more cultural, not because --

00:54:16.960 --> 00:54:18.800
for a few reasons, I'll explain.

00:54:18.800 --> 00:54:22.010
There is no cases where
there was actually a Muslim

00:54:22.010 --> 00:54:24.220
who was polygamist, right.

00:54:24.220 --> 00:54:28.760
So it's not the reality of being
polygamist, it was the concept

00:54:28.760 --> 00:54:30.960
that Muslims could be polygamist,

00:54:30.960 --> 00:54:34.250
because the religion
permitted up to 4 wives.

00:54:34.250 --> 00:54:36.170
Well, this was the argument.

00:54:36.170 --> 00:54:40.060
And so I believe that it wasn't
the practice of religion,

00:54:40.060 --> 00:54:43.050
I believe it was the
perception of religion.

00:54:43.050 --> 00:54:47.330
And that's why I consider
it more cultural.

00:54:47.330 --> 00:54:52.330
Now, they can go back to the Koran
and say, oh, but it says this.

00:54:52.330 --> 00:54:56.380
It's based on a religious
tenant, but there were no cases

00:54:56.380 --> 00:54:59.460
where there really was a
Muslim who was polygamist,

00:54:59.460 --> 00:55:03.340
who was turned away, right.

00:55:03.340 --> 00:55:06.960
So that's why I sort of think it's
the way in which Islam was viewed

00:55:06.960 --> 00:55:15.510
from the outside, rather than
experienced within the US.

